opment/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/manual_testing_playbook/03--validation/mk-deep-loop-guard.md:\n  Line 69: | `.opencode/plugins/mk-deep-loop-guard.js` | OpenCode plugin entrypoint; registers and implements the `tool.execute.before` hook. |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/z_archive/cli-codex-retired/references/agent_delegation.md:\n  Line 67: Codex CLI tasks are routed using the `-p` / `--profile` flag with a profile name. Profiles are defined in `config.toml` under `[profiles.<name>]` sections. For git diff reviews, use the built-in `codex exec review` subcommand.\n\n  Line 96: Profiles must be defined in `config.toml`. Example configuration matching the agent catalog below:\n\n  Line 99: # .codex/config.toml\n\n  Line 125: **Note:** The `.codex/agents/*.toml` files define agent personas for the interactive multi-agent TUI feature. They are NOT loaded by the `-p` profile flag. To use agent-specific behavior in `codex exec`, define corresponding `[profiles.<name>]` sections in config.toml and include context in the prompt.\n\n  Line 324: | Profile not found   | Error: profile not defined          | Verify profile name matches `[profiles.<name>]` in config.toml |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/z_archive/cli-codex-retired/references/hook_contract.md:\n  Line 38: Superset `codex` wrapper already passes this flag, but `~/.codex/config.toml`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/z_archive/cli-codex-retired/references/cli_reference.md:\n  Line 37: - Configuring agents via `.codex/agents/*.toml`\n\n  Line 112: | `--config` | `-c` | `key=value` | Override a config.toml value (e.g., `-c model_reasoning_effort=\"high\"`) |\n\n  Line 125: | `--profile <name>` / `-p` | Load a named configuration profile from `[profiles.<name>]` in config.toml |\n\n  Line 146: The `-c` / `--config` flag overrides any `config.toml` value at runtime. Uses dotted paths for nested values. The value is parsed as TOML; if parsing fails, it's used as a literal string.\n\n  Line 205: 2. **config.toml:** `model_reasoning_effort = \"medium\"` (global default matching the skill)\n\n  Line 251: # .codex/agents/my-agent.toml — reasoning-heavy agent\n\n  Line 254: # .codex/agents/my-codegen-agent.toml — code-focused agent\n\n  Line 394: ├── config.toml          # Global CLI configuration\n\n  Line 397:     ├── context.toml\n\n  Line 398:     ├── debug.toml\n\n  Line 399:     ├── handover.toml\n\n  Line 400:     ├── orchestrate.toml\n\n  Line 401:     ├── deep-research.toml\n\n  Line 402:     ├── review.toml\n\n  Line 403:     ├── speckit.toml\n\n  Line 404:     ├── ai-council.toml\n\n  Line 405:     └── write.toml\n\n  Line 408: ### config.toml Format\n\n  Line 411: # .codex/config.toml\n\n  Line 420: Each agent is a `.toml` file in `.codex/agents/`. Fields:\n\n  Line 423: # .codex/agents/example.toml\n\n  Line 455: Named profiles allow switching between preset configurations. Profiles are defined in `config.toml` under `[profiles.<name>]` sections:\n\n  Line 458: # ~/.codex/config.toml or .codex/config.toml\n\n  Line 473: **Note:** The `.codex/agents/*.toml` files define agent personas for the interactive multi-agent TUI feature (requires `multi_agent` feature flag). They are NOT loaded by the `-p` profile flag. To use agent-specific settings in `codex exec`, define corresponding `[profiles.<name>]` sections in config.toml.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/assets/prompt_templates.md:\n  Line 372: **Agent:** `ai-council` (`mode: subagent` — dispatched via `orchestrate` or `/deep:ai-council`, never direct top-level `--agent ai-council`)\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md:\n  Line 292: 2. **`ai-council`** — dispatched either via its own `/deep:ai-council` command or via `orchestrate`'s registry-backed Task-dispatch. Direct `--agent ai-council` is rejected at the top level (`mode: subagent`); route through `/deep:ai-council` or `--agent orchestrate` with an ai-council-shaped prompt.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-prompt/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md:\n  Line 25: | `.agents/commands/create/prompt.toml` | Modified | Fixed stale refs, added Step 1a interactive behavior |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/references/stack_detection.md:\n  Line 50: [ -f \"wrangler.toml\" ]\n\n  Line 58: **Generic-Node guard**: WEBFLOW markers are gated to actual Webflow signals (vendor globals, Webflow paths, `wrangler.toml`, `src/2_javascript/`). Bare Motion package imports and generic Motion documentation mentions are MOTION_DEV intent signals after surface selection, not WEBFLOW surface markers. Generic Node.js outside `.opencode/` and without WEBFLOW markers stays UNKNOWN until the user clarifies the surface.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/SKILL.md:\n  Line 103:      || [[ -f \"wrangler.toml\" ]]; then\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:\n  Line 35: - WEBFLOW surface detection (vanilla HTML/CSS/JS frontend with motion.dev / GSAP / Lenis / HLS / Swiper / FilePond markers, `wrangler.toml`, `src/2_javascript/`).\n\n  Line 72: 5. The operator uses sandboxed scratch paths under `/tmp/skc-NNN-sandbox/` for any file fixtures the scenarios need (e.g. fake `wrangler.toml` to trigger WEBFLOW detection).\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/manual_testing_playbook/04--agent-routing/multi-ai-council-multi-strategy.md:\n  Line 51: | CO-017 | Ultra-think multi-strategy planning | Confirm `--agent orchestrate` dispatching `@ai-council` produces 3+ distinct strategies scored across 3+ dimensions with no file writes | `As an external-AI conductor planning a CommonJS-to-ESM migration of a single hypothetical module, dispatch --agent orchestrate with a request for @ai-council to compare three strategies (big-bang rewrite, incremental wrapper, dual-build). Verify the response presents three distinct strategies, scores each across risk/effort/timeline/reversibility, recommends one with rationale, and does NOT modify any files in the repo. Return a concise pass/fail verdict naming the recommended strategy and the dimension count per strategy.` | 1. `bash: stat -f '%m %N' .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/cli_reference.md > /tmp/co-017-mtimes-before.txt && cat /tmp/co-017-mtimes-before.txt` -> 2. `bash: opencode run --model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro --agent orchestrate --variant high --format json --dir \"$(pwd)\" \"Dispatch @ai-council: compare three strategies for migrating a single CommonJS Node module to ESM: (1) big-bang rewrite, (2) incremental wrapper, (3) dual-build. Score each across risk, effort, timeline, and reversibility. Recommend one with rationale. PLANNING-ONLY — do not modify any files.\" > /tmp/co-017-events.jsonl 2>&1` -> 3. `bash: echo \"Exit: $?\"` -> 4. `bash: stat -f '%m %N' .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/references/cli_reference.md > /tmp/co-017-mtimes-after.txt && diff /tmp/co-017-mtimes-before.txt /tmp/co-017-mtimes-after.txt && echo SENTINEL_MTIMES_OK` -> 5. `bash: jq -r 'select(.type == \"tool.call\") \\| .payload.name' /tmp/co-017-events.jsonl \\| grep -ciE '(Edit\\|Write)'` -> 6. `bash: jq -r 'select(.type == \"message.delta\" or .type == \"session.completed\") \\| .payload' /tmp/co-017-events.jsonl \\| grep -ciE '(big-bang\\|incremental wrapper\\|dual-build)'` -> 7. `bash: jq -r 'select(.type == \"message.del...\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/07--cross-stack-routing/decision-matrix-routing.md:\n  Line 48: 2. If `WEBFLOW` is selected, verify the prompt contains no Webflow path, vendor global, or `wrangler.toml`.\n\n\n(Results truncated. Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":100,"truncated":true},"title":"--agent ai-council|\\.opencode/agents/\\*\\.toml|mk-deep-loop-guard\\.js|MIRROR_TEMPLATES|\\.toml","time":{"start":1782925249219,"end":1782925249241}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0bc63f1141a1970e016a4547c11fc081919a19a71465a67213"}},"id":"prt_f1ea04aba001bzI5BXJdEw35F2","sessionID":"ses_0e161eb82ffeyXiRWhaMw6c4O7","messageID":"msg_f1e9ff6c3001zorzGQvtwi4X4c"}}
