{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782925288968,"sessionID":"ses_0e161eb82ffeyXiRWhaMw6c4O7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_bEuY7bjAVlINbPYjF0rL42ST","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md","offset":25,"limit":60},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n25: \n26: ### Activation Triggers\n27: \n28: - **Full plugin / skill / MCP runtime** (use case 1) — calling AI is Claude Code / OpenCode / Copilot / raw shell AND the task needs the project's full Spec Kit Memory database, Code Graph semantic index, structural code graph, or every plugin/skill/MCP tool in a one-shot dispatch. Includes `@deep-research` / `@deep-review` agent loops with externalized state under `.opencode/specs/`.\n29: - **Parallel detached session** (use case 2) — operator already inside OpenCode (TUI / web / serve / acp) AND wants a SEPARATE session with its own session id and state directory for ablation, worker farm, or parallel research. Prompt explicitly mentions \"parallel detached\", \"ablation suite\", \"worker farm\", \"parallel research\", \"spawn detached\", or \"share URL\".\n30: - **Cross-AI orchestration handback** (use case 3) — calling AI is non-Anthropic (OpenCode / Copilot), task targets a project-specific subsystem (spec-kit, memory, code-graph, advisor), and the non-Anthropic CLI cannot load the project's plugin/skill/MCP runtime on its own and needs OpenCode as a bridge. When the caller only needs a daemon-backed tool call, prefer the shipped front doors (`spec-memory.cjs`, `code-index.cjs`, `skill-advisor.cjs`) over a full `opencode run` delegation.\n31: - **Agent dispatch** — task matches a specialized OpenCode agent. Primary agents (directly invokable via `--agent`): `general`, `plan` (built-in), `orchestrate`. Generic subagents fully dispatched via the orchestrate primary: `context`, `review`, `write`, `debug`, `ai-council`. Command-owned loop executors (`deep-research`, `deep-review`, `deep-improvement`, `prompt-improver`) are owned end-to-end by their parent `/deep:*` command; `orchestrate` may perform exactly one bounded hand-off dispatch to a recognized loop request, but never manages the loop itself. See §3 \"OpenCode Agent Delegation\" for the full contract.\n32: - **Cross-repo dispatch** — session in repo A dispatches into repo B's plugin/skill/MCP runtime via `--dir <path>` or remote OpenCode server via `--attach <url>`.\n33: \n34: ### When NOT to Use\n35: \n36: - **You ARE OpenCode already.** If your runtime is OpenCode (detection signal: `$OPENCODE_CONFIG_DIR` or any `OPENCODE_*` env var set, `opencode` in process ancestry, or `~/.opencode/state/<id>/lock` present), this skill refuses to load. Self-invocation creates a circular dispatch loop and burns tokens for no value. The cli-X family is exclusively for cross-AI delegation. The single legitimate exception is an explicit \"parallel detached\" request that intentionally spawns a SEPARATE session id and state directory (use case 2); without that qualifier, the smart router refuses per ADR-001.\n37: - Simple, quick tasks where `opencode run` overhead is not worth it.\n38: - Tasks that only need a raw model dispatch — use a sibling cli-* skill.\n39: - Tasks requiring interactive TUI or web UI (use `opencode` directly instead of `opencode run`).\n40: - Context already loaded and understood by the calling AI.\n41: - Tasks where the OpenCode binary is not installed at the expected path.\n42: \n43: ---\n44: \n45: ## 2. SMART ROUTING\n46: \n47: \n48: ### Prerequisite Detection\n49: \n50: ```bash\n51: # Verify OpenCode CLI is available\n52: command -v opencode || echo \"Not installed. Run: brew install opencode (macOS) or curl -fsSL https://opencode.ai/install | bash\"\n53: \n54: # SELF-INVOCATION GUARD (ADR-001 layered detection)\n55: # Layer 1: env var lookup — any OPENCODE_* variable\n56: env | grep -q '^OPENCODE_' && echo \"ERROR: OPENCODE_* env detected — already inside OpenCode.\"\n57: # Layer 2: process ancestry — opencode in parent tree\n58: ps -o command= -p \"$PPID\" | grep -q opencode && echo \"ERROR: opencode parent process detected.\"\n59: # Layer 3: state lock-file probe\n60: ls ~/.opencode/state/*/lock 2>/dev/null | head -1 | grep -q lock && echo \"ERROR: live OpenCode session lock detected.\"\n61: ```\n62: \n63: ### Self-Invocation Guard (ADR-001)\n64: \n65: ```python\n66: def detect_self_invocation():\n67:     \"\"\"Returns a non-None signal when the orchestrator is already running inside OpenCode.\"\"\"\n68:     # Layer 1: env var lookup — OpenCode sets OPENCODE_CONFIG_DIR and OPENCODE_* vars\n69:     for key in os.environ:\n70:         if key == 'OPENCODE_CONFIG_DIR' or key.startswith('OPENCODE_'):\n71:             return ('env', key)\n72:     # Layer 2: process ancestry — opencode in parent tree\n73:     try:\n74:         ancestry = subprocess.check_output(['ps', '-o', 'command=', '-p', str(os.getppid())]).decode()\n75:         if '/opencode' in ancestry or 'opencode ' in ancestry:\n76:             return ('ancestry', 'opencode')\n77:     except subprocess.SubprocessError:\n78:         pass\n79:     # Layer 3: state lock-file probe\n80:     state_dir = os.path.expanduser('~/.opencode/state')\n81:     if os.path.isdir(state_dir):\n82:         for entry in os.listdir(state_dir):\n83:             if os.path.exists(os.path.join(state_dir, entry, 'lock')):\n84:                 return ('lockfile', entry)\n\n(Showing lines 25-84 of 443. Use offset=85 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\n### Activation Triggers\n\n- **Full plugin / skill / MCP runtime** (use case 1) — calling AI is Claude Code / OpenCode / Copilot / raw shell AND the task needs the project's full Spec Kit Memory database, Code Graph semantic index, structural code graph, or every plugin/skill/MCP tool in a one-shot dispatch. Includes `@deep-research` / `@deep-review` agent loops with externalized state under `.opencode/specs/`.\n- **Parallel detached session** (use case 2) — operator already inside OpenCode (TUI / web / serve / acp) AND wants a SEPARATE session with its own session id and state directory for ablation, worker farm, or parallel research. Prompt explicitly mentions \"parallel detached\", \"ablation suite\", \"worker farm\", \"parallel research\", \"spawn detached\", or \"share URL\".\n- **Cross-AI orchestration handback** (use case 3) — calling AI is non-Anthropic (OpenCode / Copilot), task targets a project-specific subsystem (spec-kit, memory, code-graph, advisor), and the non-Anthropic CLI cannot load the project's plugin/skill/MCP runtime on its own and needs OpenCode as a bridge. When the caller only needs a daemon-backed tool call, prefer the shipped front doors (`spec-memory.cjs`, `code-index.cjs`, `skill-advisor.cjs`) over a full `opencode run` delegation.\n- **Agent dispatch** — task matches a specialized OpenCode agent. Primary agents (directly invokable via `--agent`): `general`, `plan` (built-in), `orchestrate`. Generic subagents fully dispatched via the orchestrate primary: `context`, `review`, `write`, `debug`, `ai-council`. Command-owned loop executors (`deep-research`, `deep-review`, `deep-improvement`, `prompt-improver`) are owned end-to-end by their parent `/deep:*` command; `orchestrate` may perform exactly one bounded hand-off dispatch to a recognized loop request, but never manages the loop itself. See §3 \"OpenCode Agent Delegation\" for the full contract.\n- **Cross-repo dispatch** — session in repo A dispatches into repo B's plugin/skill/MCP runtime via `--dir <path>` or remote OpenCode server via `--attach <url>`.\n\n### When NOT to Use\n\n- **You ARE OpenCode already.** If your runtime is OpenCode (detection signal: `$OPENCODE_CONFIG_DIR` or any `OPENCODE_*` env var set, `opencode` in process ancestry, or `~/.opencode/state/<id>/lock` present), this skill refuses to load. Self-invocation creates a circular dispatch loop and burns tokens for no value. The cli-X family is exclusively for cross-AI delegation. The single legitimate exception is an explicit \"parallel detached\" request that intentionally spawns a SEPARATE session id and state directory (use case 2); without that qualifier, the smart router refuses per ADR-001.\n- Simple, quick tasks where `opencode run` overhead is not worth it.\n- Tasks that only need a raw model dispatch — use a sibling cli-* skill.\n- Tasks requiring interactive TUI or web UI (use `opencode` directly instead of `opencode run`).\n- Context already loaded and understood by the calling AI.\n- Tasks where the OpenCode binary is not installed at the expected path.\n\n---\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md","text":"\n### Activation Triggers\n\n- **Full plugin / skill / MCP runtime** (use case 1) — calling AI is Claude Code / OpenCode / Copilot / raw shell AND the task needs the project's full Spec Kit Memory database, Code Graph semantic index, structural code graph, or every plugin/skill/MCP tool in a one-shot dispatch. Includes `@deep-research` / `@deep-review` agent loops with externalized state under `.opencode/specs/`.\n- **Parallel detached session** (use case 2) — operator already inside OpenCode (TUI / web / serve / acp) AND wants a SEPARATE session with its own session id and state directory for ablation, worker farm, or parallel research. Prompt explicitly mentions \"parallel detached\", \"ablation suite\", \"worker farm\", \"parallel research\", \"spawn detached\", or \"share URL\".\n- **Cross-AI orchestration handback** (use case 3) — calling AI is non-Anthropic (OpenCode / Copilot), task targets a project-specific subsystem (spec-kit, memory, code-graph, advisor), and the non-Anthropic CLI cannot load the project's plugin/skill/MCP runtime on its own and needs OpenCode as a bridge. When the caller only needs a daemon-backed tool call, prefer the shipped front doors (`spec-memory.cjs`, `code-index.cjs`, `skill-advisor.cjs`) over a full `opencode run` delegation.\n- **Agent dispatch** — task matches a specialized OpenCode agent. Primary agents (directly invokable via `--agent`): `general`, `plan` (built-in), `orchestrate`. Generic subagents fully dispatched via the orchestrate primary: `context`, `review`, `write`, `debug`, `ai-council`. Command-owned loop executors (`deep-research`, `deep-review`, `deep-improvement`, `prompt-improver`) are owned end-to-end by their parent `/deep:*` command; `orchestrate` may perform exactly one bounded hand-off dispatch to a recognized loop request, but never manages the loop itself. See §3 \"OpenCode Agent Delegation\" for the full contract.\n- **Cross-repo dispatch** — session in repo A dispatches into repo B's plugin/skill/MCP runtime via `--dir <path>` or remote OpenCode server via `--attach <url>`.\n\n### When NOT to Use\n\n- **You ARE OpenCode already.** If your runtime is OpenCode (detection signal: `$OPENCODE_CONFIG_DIR` or any `OPENCODE_*` env var set, `opencode` in process ancestry, or `~/.opencode/state/<id>/lock` present), this skill refuses to load. Self-invocation creates a circular dispatch loop and burns tokens for no value. The cli-X family is exclusively for cross-AI delegation. The single legitimate exception is an explicit \"parallel detached\" request that intentionally spawns a SEPARATE session id and state directory (use case 2); without that qualifier, the smart router refuses per ADR-001.\n- Simple, quick tasks where `opencode run` overhead is not worth it.\n- Tasks that only need a raw model dispatch — use a sibling cli-* skill.\n- Tasks requiring interactive TUI or web UI (use `opencode` directly instead of `opencode run`).\n- Context already loaded and understood by the calling AI.\n- Tasks where the OpenCode binary is not installed at the expected path.\n\n---\n\n## 2. SMART ROUTING\n\n\n### Prerequisite Detection\n\n```bash\n# Verify OpenCode CLI is available\ncommand -v opencode || echo \"Not installed. Run: brew install opencode (macOS) or curl -fsSL https://opencode.ai/install | bash\"\n\n# SELF-INVOCATION GUARD (ADR-001 layered detection)\n# Layer 1: env var lookup — any OPENCODE_* variable\nenv | grep -q '^OPENCODE_' && echo \"ERROR: OPENCODE_* env detected — already inside OpenCode.\"\n# Layer 2: process ancestry — opencode in parent tree\nps -o command= -p \"$PPID\" | grep -q opencode && echo \"ERROR: opencode parent process detected.\"\n# Layer 3: state lock-file probe\nls ~/.opencode/state/*/lock 2>/dev/null | head -1 | grep -q lock && echo \"ERROR: live OpenCode session lock detected.\"\n```\n\n### Self-Invocation Guard (ADR-001)\n\n```python\ndef detect_self_invocation():\n    \"\"\"Returns a non-None signal when the orchestrator is already running inside OpenCode.\"\"\"\n    # Layer 1: env var lookup — OpenCode sets OPENCODE_CONFIG_DIR and OPENCODE_* vars\n    for key in os.environ:\n        if key == 'OPENCODE_CONFIG_DIR' or key.startswith('OPENCODE_'):\n            return ('env', key)\n    # Layer 2: process ancestry — opencode in parent tree\n    try:\n        ancestry = subprocess.check_output(['ps', '-o', 'command=', '-p', str(os.getppid())]).decode()\n        if '/opencode' in ancestry or 'opencode ' in ancestry:\n            return ('ancestry', 'opencode')\n    except subprocess.SubprocessError:\n        pass\n    # Layer 3: state lock-file probe\n    state_dir = os.path.expanduser('~/.opencode/state')\n    if os.path.isdir(state_dir):\n        for entry in os.listdir(state_dir):\n            if os.path.exists(os.path.join(state_dir, entry, 'lock')):\n                return ('lockfile', entry)","lineStart":25,"lineEnd":84,"totalLines":443,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md","time":{"start":1782925288963,"end":1782925288966}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_097401b0ddfbf38d016a4547e8ddc08191b4bfe8f42652b48a"}},"id":"prt_f1ea0e5c9001ZVhg7o8FD0YB5U","sessionID":"ses_0e161eb82ffeyXiRWhaMw6c4O7","messageID":"msg_f1ea04e9e001ZmIr7o6tsOX1oD"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782925288973,"sessionID":"ses_0e161eb82ffeyXiRWhaMw6c4O7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_N9be4BvPYKXUFwfl5S1Bp4ye","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md","offset":275,"limit":35},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n275: Run `opencode providers list` to confirm credentials and `opencode models <provider>` for live choices. Default to `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro --variant high` (direct DeepSeek API); the MiniMax Token Plan default `minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3` (omit `--agent`), the pay-per-token `minimax/MiniMax-M3` (Direct API), `xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro --variant high` (Xiaomi Token Plan Europe — MiMo; high reasoning preset; omit `--agent`), `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro --variant high` (Xiaomi Direct API — MiMo; pay-per-token) and `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed --variant high` (low-latency MiMo tier, same prompt contract) remain available. The Kimi For Coding plan model `kimi-for-coding/k2p7` (\"Kimi K2.7 Code\"; 256k / 262,144-token context; subscription billing — dispatch cost 0; omit `--agent`; `--variant high` accepted but effect benchmark-unverified) is the coding-optimized large-context Kimi path. **Operational caveat (observed 2026-06-17):** on broad / large-repo scopes at `--variant high`, k2p7 over-explores (many sequential reads) and can exceed a 600s timeout WITHOUT emitting — opencode flushes only the final assistant message to stdout, so a killed run yields 0 bytes (looks like a hang, but it was working). Mitigate with a hard read-cap in the prompt (\"read ≤N files then emit\") + a 1200s+ timeout, or omit `--variant`. The Z.AI GLM Coding Plan model `zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2` (\"GLM-5.2\"; flagship long-horizon coding; 1,000,000-token context / 131,072 output per Z.AI docs; subscription billing; omit `--agent`; `--variant`↔`reasoning_effort` mapping unverified — GLM has native high/max, smoke-test before relying on it; thinking on by default + preserved on the Coding Plan endpoint) is the Z.AI direct-provider GLM path, superseding the gateway-only `glm-5.1` removed in v1.3.15.0; confirm the live slug via `opencode models zai-coding-plan`. **Operational (benchmark 008, n=45):** thinking-on drives latency variance 6–161s (avg ~26s) — budget generous timeouts; expect ~1/45... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n276: \n277: Shared small-model facts, context defaults, quota pools, and fallback targets live in `../sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json`.\n278: \n279: ### OpenCode Agent Delegation\n280: \n281: The calling AI is the conductor. OpenCode distinguishes **primary agents** (directly invokable via `--agent <slug>`) from **subagents** (dispatched as Task-tool subagents from a primary).\n282: \n283: #### Primary agents — directly invokable via `--agent`\n284: \n285: OpenCode defines `general`, `plan`, and `orchestrate` as primary agents. **Caveat — never pass `--agent general`:** the current opencode treats `general` as a subagent and rejects it at the top level, and the default agent (used when no `--agent` is given) already covers that case. Pin `--agent plan|orchestrate` only when the task needs that profile AND `opencode run --help` on the installed version confirms top-level acceptance; otherwise state the role in the prompt body.\n286: \n287: #### Subagents — dispatched as Task subagents from a primary\n288: \n289: These live at `.opencode/agents/<slug>.md` with `mode: subagent` and are NOT directly invokable via `opencode run --agent`. Three dispatch surfaces are legal under the single-hop NDP contract:\n290: \n291: 1. **Generic subagents** (`context`, `review`, `write`, `debug`) — dispatched by a primary (`orchestrate`) using the Task tool. To exercise via the opencode CLI, route through `--agent orchestrate` and let it dispatch the relevant subagent.\n292: 2. **`ai-council`** — dispatched either via its own `/deep:ai-council` command or via `orchestrate`'s registry-backed Task-dispatch. Direct `--agent ai-council` is rejected at the top level (`mode: subagent`); route through `/deep:ai-council` or `--agent orchestrate` with an ai-council-shaped prompt.\n293: 3. **Command-owned loop executors** (`deep-research`, `deep-review`, `deep-improvement`, `prompt-improver`) — LOOP-OWNED by their parent commands (`/deep:research`, `/deep:review`, `/deep:agent-improvement`, `/prompt`), which own iteration state, convergence detection, and continuity. Never dispatch these directly via raw `--agent <slug>` from the CLI. `orchestrate` is an authorized **caller/coordinator only** for these agents (e.g. its registry-backed `/deep:review` Priority row) — it may perform exactly one bounded hand-off dispatch to the resolved leaf, but MUST NOT re-implement the loop (no iterating, no convergence checks, no continuity tracking); that remains the parent command's job.\n294: \n295: Generic subagents (`context`, `review`, `write`, `debug`) and `ai-council` route through `orchestrate` for full Task-tool dispatch; loop executors (`deep-research`, `deep-review`, `deep-improvement`, `prompt-improver`) are loop-owned by their parent commands, with `orchestrate` limited to a single bounded hand-off when it recognizes one of these as the target.\n296: \n297: See [agent_delegation.md](./references/agent_delegation.md) for the complete agent roster and dispatch patterns.\n298: \n299: ### Unique OpenCode Strengths\n300: \n301: OpenCode dispatch provides full project runtime loading, detached sessions, JSON event streams, agent routing, cross-repo/server dispatch, session continuation, and plugin-disable debugging.\n302: \n303: ### Essential Commands\n304: \n305: Use the default invocation for external runtime handback, append `--share --port <N>` only for explicit detached sessions, select `--agent orchestrate` for generic subagent routing, and change `--dir` for cross-repo dispatch.\n306: \n307: ### Error Handling\n308: \n309: Install missing binaries, refuse ambiguous self-invocation, run provider pre-flight for model/auth errors, check version drift for unknown flags, force `--format json` for empty streams, add `</dev/null` for background loops, confirm `--share`, use `--pure` only for plugin crashes, and inspect state logs for stuck sessions.\n\n(Showing lines 275-309 of 443. Use offset=310 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"Run `opencode providers list` to confirm credentials and `opencode models <provider>` for live choices. Default to `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro --variant high` (direct DeepSeek API); the MiniMax Token Plan default `minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3` (omit `--agent`), the pay-per-token `minimax/MiniMax-M3` (Direct API), `xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro --variant high` (Xiaomi Token Plan Europe — MiMo; high reasoning preset; omit `--agent`), `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro --variant high` (Xiaomi Direct API — MiMo; pay-per-token) and `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed --variant high` (low-latency MiMo tier, same prompt contract) remain available. The Kimi For Coding plan model `kimi-for-coding/k2p7` (\"Kimi K2.7 Code\"; 256k / 262,144-token context; subscription billing — dispatch cost 0; omit `--agent`; `--variant high` accepted but effect benchmark-unverified) is the coding-optimized large-context Kimi path. **Operational caveat (observed 2026-06-17):** on broad / large-repo scopes at `--variant high`, k2p7 over-explores (many sequential reads) and can exceed a 600s timeout WITHOUT emitting — opencode flushes only the final assistant message to stdout, so a killed run yields 0 bytes (looks like a hang, but it was working). Mitigate with a hard read-cap in the prompt (\"read ≤N files then emit\") + a 1200s+ timeout, or omit `--variant`. The Z.AI GLM Coding Plan model `zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2` (\"GLM-5.2\"; flagship long-horizon coding; 1,000,000-token context / 131,072 output per Z.AI docs; subscription billing; omit `--agent`; `--variant`↔`reasoning_effort` mapping unverified — GLM has native high/max, smoke-test before relying on it; thinking on by default + preserved on the Coding Plan endpoint) is the Z.AI direct-provider GLM path, superseding the gateway-only `glm-5.1` removed in v1.3.15.0; confirm the live slug via `opencode models zai-coding-plan`. **Operational (benchmark 008, n=45):** thinking-on drives latency variance 6–161s (avg ~26s) — budget generous timeouts; expect ~1/45... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n\nShared small-model facts, context defaults, quota pools, and fallback targets live in `../sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json`.\n\n### OpenCode Agent Delegation\n\nThe calling AI is the conductor. OpenCode distinguishes **primary agents** (directly invokable via `--agent <slug>`) from **subagents** (dispatched as Task-tool subagents from a primary).\n\n#### Primary agents — directly invokable via `--agent`\n\nOpenCode defines `general`, `plan`, and `orchestrate` as primary agents. **Caveat — never pass `--agent general`:** the current opencode treats `general` as a subagent and rejects it at the top level, and the default agent (used when no `--agent` is given) already covers that case. Pin `--agent plan|orchestrate` only when the task needs that profile AND `opencode run --help` on the installed version confirms top-level acceptance; otherwise state the role in the prompt body.\n\n#### Subagents — dispatched as Task subagents from a primary\n\nThese live at `.opencode/agents/<slug>.md` with `mode: subagent` and are NOT directly invokable via `opencode run --agent`. Three dispatch surfaces are legal under the single-hop NDP contract:\n\n1. **Generic subagents** (`context`, `review`, `write`, `debug`) — dispatched by a primary (`orchestrate`) using the Task tool. To exercise via the opencode CLI, route through `--agent orchestrate` and let it dispatch the relevant subagent.\n2. **`ai-council`** — dispatched either via its own `/deep:ai-council` command or via `orchestrate`'s registry-backed Task-dispatch. Direct `--agent ai-council` is rejected at the top level (`mode: subagent`); route through `/deep:ai-council` or `--agent orchestrate` with an ai-council-shaped prompt.\n3. **Command-owned loop executors** (`deep-research`, `deep-review`, `deep-improvement`, `prompt-improver`) — LOOP-OWNED by their parent commands (`/deep:research`, `/deep:review`, `/deep:agent-improvement`, `/prompt`), which own iteration state, convergence detection, and continuity. Never dispatch these directly via raw `--agent <slug>` from the CLI. `orchestrate` is an authorized **caller/coordinator only** for these agents (e.g. its registry-backed `/deep:review` Priority row) — it may perform exactly one bounded hand-off dispatch to the resolved leaf, but MUST NOT re-implement the loop (no iterating, no convergence checks, no continuity tracking); that remains the parent command's job.\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md","text":"Run `opencode providers list` to confirm credentials and `opencode models <provider>` for live choices. Default to `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro --variant high` (direct DeepSeek API); the MiniMax Token Plan default `minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3` (omit `--agent`), the pay-per-token `minimax/MiniMax-M3` (Direct API), `xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro --variant high` (Xiaomi Token Plan Europe — MiMo; high reasoning preset; omit `--agent`), `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro --variant high` (Xiaomi Direct API — MiMo; pay-per-token) and `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed --variant high` (low-latency MiMo tier, same prompt contract) remain available. The Kimi For Coding plan model `kimi-for-coding/k2p7` (\"Kimi K2.7 Code\"; 256k / 262,144-token context; subscription billing — dispatch cost 0; omit `--agent`; `--variant high` accepted but effect benchmark-unverified) is the coding-optimized large-context Kimi path. **Operational caveat (observed 2026-06-17):** on broad / large-repo scopes at `--variant high`, k2p7 over-explores (many sequential reads) and can exceed a 600s timeout WITHOUT emitting — opencode flushes only the final assistant message to stdout, so a killed run yields 0 bytes (looks like a hang, but it was working). Mitigate with a hard read-cap in the prompt (\"read ≤N files then emit\") + a 1200s+ timeout, or omit `--variant`. The Z.AI GLM Coding Plan model `zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2` (\"GLM-5.2\"; flagship long-horizon coding; 1,000,000-token context / 131,072 output per Z.AI docs; subscription billing; omit `--agent`; `--variant`↔`reasoning_effort` mapping unverified — GLM has native high/max, smoke-test before relying on it; thinking on by default + preserved on the Coding Plan endpoint) is the Z.AI direct-provider GLM path, superseding the gateway-only `glm-5.1` removed in v1.3.15.0; confirm the live slug via `opencode models zai-coding-plan`. **Operational (benchmark 008, n=45):** thinking-on drives latency variance 6–161s (avg ~26s) — budget generous timeouts; expect ~1/45... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n\nShared small-model facts, context defaults, quota pools, and fallback targets live in `../sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json`.\n\n### OpenCode Agent Delegation\n\nThe calling AI is the conductor. OpenCode distinguishes **primary agents** (directly invokable via `--agent <slug>`) from **subagents** (dispatched as Task-tool subagents from a primary).\n\n#### Primary agents — directly invokable via `--agent`\n\nOpenCode defines `general`, `plan`, and `orchestrate` as primary agents. **Caveat — never pass `--agent general`:** the current opencode treats `general` as a subagent and rejects it at the top level, and the default agent (used when no `--agent` is given) already covers that case. Pin `--agent plan|orchestrate` only when the task needs that profile AND `opencode run --help` on the installed version confirms top-level acceptance; otherwise state the role in the prompt body.\n\n#### Subagents — dispatched as Task subagents from a primary\n\nThese live at `.opencode/agents/<slug>.md` with `mode: subagent` and are NOT directly invokable via `opencode run --agent`. Three dispatch surfaces are legal under the single-hop NDP contract:\n\n1. **Generic subagents** (`context`, `review`, `write`, `debug`) — dispatched by a primary (`orchestrate`) using the Task tool. To exercise via the opencode CLI, route through `--agent orchestrate` and let it dispatch the relevant subagent.\n2. **`ai-council`** — dispatched either via its own `/deep:ai-council` command or via `orchestrate`'s registry-backed Task-dispatch. Direct `--agent ai-council` is rejected at the top level (`mode: subagent`); route through `/deep:ai-council` or `--agent orchestrate` with an ai-council-shaped prompt.\n3. **Command-owned loop executors** (`deep-research`, `deep-review`, `deep-improvement`, `prompt-improver`) — LOOP-OWNED by their parent commands (`/deep:research`, `/deep:review`, `/deep:agent-improvement`, `/prompt`), which own iteration state, convergence detection, and continuity. Never dispatch these directly via raw `--agent <slug>` from the CLI. `orchestrate` is an authorized **caller/coordinator only** for these agents (e.g. its registry-backed `/deep:review` Priority row) — it may perform exactly one bounded hand-off dispatch to the resolved leaf, but MUST NOT re-implement the loop (no iterating, no convergence checks, no continuity tracking); that remains the parent command's job.\n\nGeneric subagents (`context`, `review`, `write`, `debug`) and `ai-council` route through `orchestrate` for full Task-tool dispatch; loop executors (`deep-research`, `deep-review`, `deep-improvement`, `prompt-improver`) are loop-owned by their parent commands, with `orchestrate` limited to a single bounded hand-off when it recognizes one of these as the target.\n\nSee [agent_delegation.md](./references/agent_delegation.md) for the complete agent roster and dispatch patterns.\n\n### Unique OpenCode Strengths\n\nOpenCode dispatch provides full project runtime loading, detached sessions, JSON event streams, agent routing, cross-repo/server dispatch, session continuation, and plugin-disable debugging.\n\n### Essential Commands\n\nUse the default invocation for external runtime handback, append `--share --port <N>` only for explicit detached sessions, select `--agent orchestrate` for generic subagent routing, and change `--dir` for cross-repo dispatch.\n\n### Error Handling\n\nInstall missing binaries, refuse ambiguous self-invocation, run provider pre-flight for model/auth errors, check version drift for unknown flags, force `--format json` for empty streams, add `</dev/null` for background loops, confirm `--share`, use `--pure` only for plugin crashes, and inspect state logs for stuck sessions.","lineStart":275,"lineEnd":309,"totalLines":443,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md","time":{"start":1782925288969,"end":1782925288972}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_097401b0ddfbf38d016a4547e8ddd88191838acc18665cbbc7"}},"id":"prt_f1ea0e60400165pRO0vv23Tf8e","sessionID":"ses_0e161eb82ffeyXiRWhaMw6c4O7","messageID":"msg_f1ea04e9e001ZmIr7o6tsOX1oD"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782925288984,"sessionID":"ses_0e161eb82ffeyXiRWhaMw6c4O7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_4wsu3EXGmEgvPHl0MHkA5heI","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/assets/prompt_templates.md","offset":360,"limit":40},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/assets/prompt_templates.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n360:   --agent general \\\n361:   --variant high \\\n362:   --format json \\\n363:   --dir /repo \\\n364:   \"<prompt>\" 2>&1\n365: ```\n366: \n367: ---\n368: \n369: ## 11. TEMPLATE 10 — MULTI-STRATEGY PLANNING VIA @MULTI-AI COUNCIL\n370: \n371: **Framework:** CRAFT\n372: **Agent:** `ai-council` (`mode: subagent` — dispatched via `orchestrate` or `/deep:ai-council`, never direct top-level `--agent ai-council`)\n373: **Use case:** 1 or 3\n374: \n375: ```text\n376: Plan the <feature / refactor> using multi-strategy comparison.\n377: \n378: Context: <one-paragraph context>\n379: Role: planning architect — no file modifications.\n380: Action: generate three distinct strategies, score each across the 5-dimension rubric, synthesize the optimal plan.\n381: Format: structured JSON plus a summary paragraph.\n382: Target: an implementation-ready plan that another agent can execute.\n383: ```\n384: \n385: ```bash\n386: opencode run \\\n387:   --model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro \\\n388:   --agent orchestrate \\\n389:   --variant high \\\n390:   --format json \\\n391:   --dir /repo \\\n392:   \"Dispatch @ai-council: <prompt>\" 2>&1\n393: ```\n394: \n395: ---\n396: \n397: ## 12. TEMPLATE 11 — DOC GENERATION VIA @WRITE\n398: \n399: **Framework:** RCAF\n\n(Showing lines 360-399 of 647. Use offset=400 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"  --agent general \\\n  --variant high \\\n  --format json \\\n  --dir /repo \\\n  \"<prompt>\" 2>&1\n```\n\n---\n\n## 11. TEMPLATE 10 — MULTI-STRATEGY PLANNING VIA @MULTI-AI COUNCIL\n\n**Framework:** CRAFT\n**Agent:** `ai-council` (`mode: subagent` — dispatched via `orchestrate` or `/deep:ai-council`, never direct top-level `--agent ai-council`)\n**Use case:** 1 or 3\n\n```text\nPlan the <feature / refactor> using multi-strategy comparison.\n\nContext: <one-paragraph context>\nRole: planning architect — no file modifications.","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/assets/prompt_templates.md","text":"  --agent general \\\n  --variant high \\\n  --format json \\\n  --dir /repo \\\n  \"<prompt>\" 2>&1\n```\n\n---\n\n## 11. TEMPLATE 10 — MULTI-STRATEGY PLANNING VIA @MULTI-AI COUNCIL\n\n**Framework:** CRAFT\n**Agent:** `ai-council` (`mode: subagent` — dispatched via `orchestrate` or `/deep:ai-council`, never direct top-level `--agent ai-council`)\n**Use case:** 1 or 3\n\n```text\nPlan the <feature / refactor> using multi-strategy comparison.\n\nContext: <one-paragraph context>\nRole: planning architect — no file modifications.\nAction: generate three distinct strategies, score each across the 5-dimension rubric, synthesize the optimal plan.\nFormat: structured JSON plus a summary paragraph.\nTarget: an implementation-ready plan that another agent can execute.\n```\n\n```bash\nopencode run \\\n  --model deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro \\\n  --agent orchestrate \\\n  --variant high \\\n  --format json \\\n  --dir /repo \\\n  \"Dispatch @ai-council: <prompt>\" 2>&1\n```\n\n---\n\n## 12. TEMPLATE 11 — DOC GENERATION VIA @WRITE\n\n**Framework:** RCAF","lineStart":360,"lineEnd":399,"totalLines":647,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/cli-opencode/assets/prompt_templates.md","time":{"start":1782925288982,"end":1782925288984}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_097401b0ddfbf38d016a4547e8dde48191ad74571203daafdb"}},"id":"prt_f1ea0e60a001AvswJ6GQINh51l","sessionID":"ses_0e161eb82ffeyXiRWhaMw6c4O7","messageID":"msg_f1ea04e9e001ZmIr7o6tsOX1oD"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782925289033,"sessionID":"ses_0e161eb82ffeyXiRWhaMw6c4O7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_vObCQhxpqiCNKCvo6tqEw89i","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/plugins/README.md","offset":1,"limit":70},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/plugins/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"OpenCode Plugin Entrypoints\"\n3: description: \"Six plugin entrypoint files OpenCode auto-loads at startup. Helper bridge modules live with their owning skills, not in this folder.\"\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # OpenCode Plugin Entrypoints\n7: \n8: OpenCode 1.3.17+ auto-loads JavaScript files in `.opencode/plugins/` at session start. This folder is intentionally limited to those entrypoint files so helper modules cannot be mistaken for plugins. Helpers and bridges live alongside their owning skills under `.opencode/skills/.../mcp_server/`.\n9: \n10: ---\n11: \n12: ## TABLE OF CONTENTS\n13: \n14: - [1. OVERVIEW](#1--overview)\n15: - [2. QUICK START](#2--quick-start)\n16: - [3. CURRENT ENTRYPOINTS](#3--current-entrypoints)\n17: - [4. BRIDGE MODULES](#4--bridge-modules)\n18: - [5. CONFIGURATION](#5--configuration)\n19: - [6. UPGRADE NOTES](#6--upgrade-notes)\n20: - [7. RELATED](#7--related)\n21: \n22: ---\n23: \n24: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n25: \n26: This folder is OpenCode's local-plugin mounting point. Every `.js` file here is auto-loaded once per session and must export a default plugin factory **and nothing else**.\n27: \n28: > **Default-export only — load-bearing.** OpenCode treats *every* export of a plugin module as its own plugin and invokes each one. A stray named export (a helper function, a constant, even a test surface) is loaded as a plugin, throws when invoked, and silently drops the **entire file** — including its real default plugin, which then never registers its tools or hooks. Keep the only `export` the `default`; hang any test surface off the default function as a property (e.g. `MyPlugin.__test = {...}`). Helper code, transports, schemas, and bridges live elsewhere so the auto-loader cannot pick up non-plugin modules.\n29: \n30: ---\n31: \n32: ## 2. QUICK START\n33: \n34: When OpenCode boots, every `.js` file in this folder is invoked once. To add a new plugin:\n35: \n36: 1. Create the entrypoint here (`my-plugin.js`) with a **default export only** — no named exports (every named export is loaded as its own plugin; see Overview). Attach any test surface as a property on the default function.\n37: 2. Co-locate any bridge / transport / schema modules under the owning skill, not here.\n38: 3. Smoke-test from both the project root and any symlinked workspace before shipping.\n39: \n40: ---\n41: \n42: ## 3. CURRENT ENTRYPOINTS\n43: \n44: | File | Role |\n45: |---|---|\n46: | `mk-skill-advisor.js` | Prompt-time Skill Advisor plugin. Surfaces a compact skill recommendation when a user prompt arrives. Routes via `mk-skill-advisor-bridge.mjs`. |\n47: | `mk-code-graph.js` | Transport-backed code-graph context plugin (OpenCode session integration). Routes context requests via `mk-code-graph-bridge.mjs`. The underlying MCP server name stays `mk-code-index` for stable tool-prefix `mcp__mk_code_index__*`. |\n48: | `mk-spec-memory.js` | Prompt-time Spec Kit Memory continuity plugin. Injects a continuity brief via `experimental.chat.system.transform` and exposes `mk_spec_memory_status`. Routes via the spec-kit warm CLI bridge. |\n49: | `mk-goal.js` | The `/goal` plugin. Owns per-session goal state (atomic, hex(sessionID)-keyed, fail-closed), injects the active goal each turn via `experimental.chat.system.transform`, exposes `mk_goal`/`mk_goal_status` tools, accounts usage over the `event()` lifecycle, and (default-off) can drive guarded autonomous continuation. Default-export only; test surface on `MkGoalPlugin.__test`. |\n50: | `mk-deep-loop-guard.js` | Detection-layer `tool.execute.before` plugin for Task-tool dispatches targeting deep-loop sub-agents. Flags (default) or blocks (`MK_DEEP_LOOP_GUARD_REJECT=1`) a Deep Route header whose declared `mode` disagrees with `mode-registry.json`'s entry for the actual `subagent_type` being dispatched. Fails open on registry read errors. |\n51: | `session-cleanup.js` | Session-end MCP cleanup plugin. OpenCode has no JSON SessionEnd hook, so this listens for the `server.instance.disposed` / `global.disposed` dispose lifecycle events and runs `.opencode/scripts/session-cleanup.sh` to reclaim the session's MCP helper descendants. Best-effort and bounded; never blocks teardown. |\n52: \n53: ---\n54: \n55: ## 4. BRIDGE MODULES\n56: \n57: Helper bridge modules are co-located with their owning skill, not in this folder:\n58: \n59: - **mk-skill-advisor** bridge: `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/plugin_bridges/mk-skill-advisor-bridge.mjs`\n60: - **mk-code-graph** bridge: `.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/plugin_bridges/mk-code-graph-bridge.mjs`\n61: - **opencode message schema**: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/plugin_bridges/spec-kit-opencode-message-schema.mjs`\n62: \n63: This keeps plugin entrypoints minimal and lets owning skills own their bridge contracts.\n64: \n65: **Naming asymmetry note:** The plugin and bridge are named `mk-code-graph` (matching the `system-code-graph` skill folder). The underlying MCP server name remains `mk-code-index` (tool prefix `mcp__mk_code_index__*`), kept stable to avoid breaking tool consumers.\n66: \n67: ---\n68: \n69: ## 5. CONFIGURATION\n70: \n\n(Showing lines 1-70 of 150. Use offset=71 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"OpenCode Plugin Entrypoints\"\ndescription: \"Six plugin entrypoint files OpenCode auto-loads at startup. Helper bridge modules live with their owning skills, not in this folder.\"\n---\n\n# OpenCode Plugin Entrypoints\n\nOpenCode 1.3.17+ auto-loads JavaScript files in `.opencode/plugins/` at session start. This folder is intentionally limited to those entrypoint files so helper modules cannot be mistaken for plugins. Helpers and bridges live alongside their owning skills under `.opencode/skills/.../mcp_server/`.\n\n---\n\n## TABLE OF CONTENTS\n\n- [1. OVERVIEW](#1--overview)\n- [2. QUICK START](#2--quick-start)\n- [3. CURRENT ENTRYPOINTS](#3--current-entrypoints)\n- [4. BRIDGE MODULES](#4--bridge-modules)\n- [5. CONFIGURATION](#5--configuration)\n- [6. UPGRADE NOTES](#6--upgrade-notes)\n- [7. RELATED](#7--related)","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/plugins/README.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"OpenCode Plugin Entrypoints\"\ndescription: \"Six plugin entrypoint files OpenCode auto-loads at startup. Helper bridge modules live with their owning skills, not in this folder.\"\n---\n\n# OpenCode Plugin Entrypoints\n\nOpenCode 1.3.17+ auto-loads JavaScript files in `.opencode/plugins/` at session start. This folder is intentionally limited to those entrypoint files so helper modules cannot be mistaken for plugins. Helpers and bridges live alongside their owning skills under `.opencode/skills/.../mcp_server/`.\n\n---\n\n## TABLE OF CONTENTS\n\n- [1. OVERVIEW](#1--overview)\n- [2. QUICK START](#2--quick-start)\n- [3. CURRENT ENTRYPOINTS](#3--current-entrypoints)\n- [4. BRIDGE MODULES](#4--bridge-modules)\n- [5. CONFIGURATION](#5--configuration)\n- [6. UPGRADE NOTES](#6--upgrade-notes)\n- [7. RELATED](#7--related)\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThis folder is OpenCode's local-plugin mounting point. Every `.js` file here is auto-loaded once per session and must export a default plugin factory **and nothing else**.\n\n> **Default-export only — load-bearing.** OpenCode treats *every* export of a plugin module as its own plugin and invokes each one. A stray named export (a helper function, a constant, even a test surface) is loaded as a plugin, throws when invoked, and silently drops the **entire file** — including its real default plugin, which then never registers its tools or hooks. Keep the only `export` the `default`; hang any test surface off the default function as a property (e.g. `MyPlugin.__test = {...}`). Helper code, transports, schemas, and bridges live elsewhere so the auto-loader cannot pick up non-plugin modules.\n\n---\n\n## 2. QUICK START\n\nWhen OpenCode boots, every `.js` file in this folder is invoked once. To add a new plugin:\n\n1. Create the entrypoint here (`my-plugin.js`) with a **default export only** — no named exports (every named export is loaded as its own plugin; see Overview). Attach any test surface as a property on the default function.\n2. Co-locate any bridge / transport / schema modules under the owning skill, not here.\n3. Smoke-test from both the project root and any symlinked workspace before shipping.\n\n---\n\n## 3. CURRENT ENTRYPOINTS\n\n| File | Role |\n|---|---|\n| `mk-skill-advisor.js` | Prompt-time Skill Advisor plugin. Surfaces a compact skill recommendation when a user prompt arrives. Routes via `mk-skill-advisor-bridge.mjs`. |\n| `mk-code-graph.js` | Transport-backed code-graph context plugin (OpenCode session integration). Routes context requests via `mk-code-graph-bridge.mjs`. The underlying MCP server name stays `mk-code-index` for stable tool-prefix `mcp__mk_code_index__*`. |\n| `mk-spec-memory.js` | Prompt-time Spec Kit Memory continuity plugin. Injects a continuity brief via `experimental.chat.system.transform` and exposes `mk_spec_memory_status`. Routes via the spec-kit warm CLI bridge. |\n| `mk-goal.js` | The `/goal` plugin. Owns per-session goal state (atomic, hex(sessionID)-keyed, fail-closed), injects the active goal each turn via `experimental.chat.system.transform`, exposes `mk_goal`/`mk_goal_status` tools, accounts usage over the `event()` lifecycle, and (default-off) can drive guarded autonomous continuation. Default-export only; test surface on `MkGoalPlugin.__test`. |\n| `mk-deep-loop-guard.js` | Detection-layer `tool.execute.before` plugin for Task-tool dispatches targeting deep-loop sub-agents. Flags (default) or blocks (`MK_DEEP_LOOP_GUARD_REJECT=1`) a Deep Route header whose declared `mode` disagrees with `mode-registry.json`'s entry for the actual `subagent_type` being dispatched. Fails open on registry read errors. |\n| `session-cleanup.js` | Session-end MCP cleanup plugin. OpenCode has no JSON SessionEnd hook, so this listens for the `server.instance.disposed` / `global.disposed` dispose lifecycle events and runs `.opencode/scripts/session-cleanup.sh` to reclaim the session's MCP helper descendants. Best-effort and bounded; never blocks teardown. |\n\n---\n\n## 4. BRIDGE MODULES\n\nHelper bridge modules are co-located with their owning skill, not in this folder:\n\n- **mk-skill-advisor** bridge: `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/plugin_bridges/mk-skill-advisor-bridge.mjs`\n- **mk-code-graph** bridge: `.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/mcp_server/plugin_bridges/mk-code-graph-bridge.mjs`\n- **opencode message schema**: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/plugin_bridges/spec-kit-opencode-message-schema.mjs`\n\nThis keeps plugin entrypoints minimal and lets owning skills own their bridge contracts.\n\n**Naming asymmetry note:** The plugin and bridge are named `mk-code-graph` (matching the `system-code-graph` skill folder). The underlying MCP server name remains `mk-code-index` (tool prefix `mcp__mk_code_index__*`), kept stable to avoid breaking tool consumers.\n\n---\n\n## 5. CONFIGURATION\n","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":70,"totalLines":150,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/plugins/README.md","time":{"start":1782925289019,"end":1782925289032}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_097401b0ddfbf38d016a4547e8ddf08191b3244cdabc5ceaf2"}},"id":"prt_f1ea0e63a0015wtdq3oSM2qixC","sessionID":"ses_0e161eb82ffeyXiRWhaMw6c4O7","messageID":"msg_f1ea04e9e001ZmIr7o6tsOX1oD"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782925289039,"sessionID":"ses_0e161eb82ffeyXiRWhaMw6c4O7","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_itTa1UtAonj3A7vuUhilt6NC","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/scan-integration.cjs","offset":1,"limit":80},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/scan-integration.cjs</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: // ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n2: // ║ scan-integration — scan agent integration surfaces across runtimes      ║\n3: // ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n4: 'use strict';\n5: \n6: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n7: // 1. IMPORTS\n8: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n9: const fs = require('node:fs');\n10: const path = require('node:path');\n11: \n12: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n13: // 2. CONSTANTS\n14: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n15: const MIRROR_TEMPLATES = [\n16:   '.opencode/agents/{name}.md',\n17:   '.claude/agents/{name}.md',\n18: ];\n19: const GLOBAL_DOC_PATHS = ['CLAUDE.md', '.claude/CLAUDE.md'];\n20: const SKILL_ADVISOR_PATH = '.opencode/skills/scripts/skill_advisor.py';\n21: \n22: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n23: // 3. HELPERS\n24: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n25: function parseArgs(argv) {\n26:   const args = {};\n27:   for (const entry of argv) {\n28:     if (!entry.startsWith('--')) continue;\n29:     const [key, ...rest] = entry.slice(